div.p:
Late Brazilian Ambassador has not been replaced; Peruvian Ambassador is
                            leaving shortly for Lima for absence of at least 3 months; there has
                            been no Colombian Ambassador for over a year; Ecuadoran Ambassador
                            announced resignation after recent change in Government of Ecuador;
                            Cuban Minister is returning to Habana, leaving no representative;
                            Venezuelan Minister plans to leave if situation does not soon clear up;
                            recalled Minister of Panama has not been replaced; Honduras is
                            represented by Chargé d’Affaires. Mexico, Uruguay and the United States
                            are still represented by Ambassadors and Nicaragua and the Dominican
                            Republic by Ministers.
